One of the main benefits of xylitol is that it can lower cavity risk. Xylitol can reduce the amount of acid produced by bacteria. When bacteria in the mouth break down sugar, they produce acid that attacks the teeth and leads to tooth decay. Xylitol doesn't allow the bacteria to produce this acid, which means it can help prevent cavities from forming. Xylitol may also help improve overall oral health by stimulating saliva production, which helps neutralize acid in the mouth and keeps the mouth hydrated. This can lead to a decrease in dry mouth, a common problem that can lead to tooth decay and other oral health issues. How can you start incorporating xylitol into your dental routine? One easy way is to use xylitol-sweetened gum or mints. Chewing gum or sucking on mints can help increase saliva production and keep your mouth hydrated. Just be sure to choose a product that contains at least 25% xylitol, as this has been shown to be the most effective concentration for preventing cavities. I personally use these four brands of gum or mints: Pur, Epic, Spry, and Zellie's. The gums contain 1g of xylitol per piece and the mints contain 0.5g of xylitol per piece. Aim for 6-10g total per day in divided exposures. You can find Pur gum at @target  #xylitol #dentaltips #cavities

Valentine’s Day 🌹 traces its roots back to Ancient Rome. ⁣ ⁣ Many associate Valentine’s Day with Saint Valentine, a third-century priest who defied Emperor Claudius II’s ban on marriages, paying the ultimate price for love. However, looking back further in time reveals a connection to the Roman pagan festival of Lupercalia, celebrated from February 13th to February 15th.⁣ ⁣ Lupercalia was a Roman festival steeped in ritualistic practices, including animal sacrifice, random couplings, and the whipping of women to bring fertility. ⁣ This event aimed to honor the mythological founders of Rome, Romulus and Remus, and took place at a sacred cave where they were believed to be nurtured by a she-wolf.⁣ 🐺🩸 ⁣ Priests, known as Luperci, conducted fertility rituals by sacrificing a goat and a dog, then using the goat’s hide to gently slap women and crop fields. Despite its seemingly barbaric nature, Roman women welcomed this act, believing it enhanced their fertility for the upcoming year. The festival also included a matchmaking ceremony where unmarried women and bachelors were paired for the duration of Lupercalia.⁣ ⁣ In the fifth century AD, Pope Gelasius I banned Lupercalia, reshaping the celebration into a day to feast and honor Saint Valentine. The Catholic Church officially declared February 14th as a day to celebrate the martyred saint, though remnants of the pagan past lingered with the inclusion of Cupid, the Roman god of desire and love, in the festivities.⁣ ⁣ 💘Cupid, originally depicted as a young man sharpening his arrows with blood from an infant, underwent a transformation during the Victorian era. Business owners sought to make Valentine’s Day more appealing to women and children, leading to the familiar image of Cupid as a pudgy baby that we recognize today.⁣ ⁣ ⁣ Valentine’s Day, with its multifaceted history blending Christian traditions and Roman pagan rituals, has evolved into a celebration of love in various forms. #pagantok #lupercalia #valentinesday2024 #ancientrome

video_description: You have to try this inspired Korean grilled cheese recipe ft. Hellmann’s Real Mayo and your Game Day leftovers 🏈!! It’s creamy, sweet and oh so cheesy 🤤 You’re gonna wanna make this over and over again 😍 #MakeTasteNotWaste #HellmannsCanadaPartner #ad  Recipe: Korean Style Grilled Cheese  ¼ cup Hellmann’s Real Mayonnaise 2 cups shredded cheese (cheddar or mozzarella) ½ tsp sugar 1 cup of your leftovers (corn, diced jalapeno poppers, diced hotdogs, etc.] ¼ cup green onions, sliced 4 slices of bread (sourdough is best) 4 tsp Hellmann’s Real Mayonnaise In a medium mixing bowl, mix the ¼ cup Hellmann’s Real Mayonnaise, shredded cheese, sugar, leftovers, and green onions together. Spread a thin layer of Hellmann’s Real Mayo on each slide of bread (½ tsp per slice).  Divide the filling among the 2 slices of bread. Then sandwich them with the other 2 slices of bread, making sure the mayo sides are facing outward.  Cover and cook your sandwiches on a skillet/griddle over medium heat for about 10 mins, making sure to flip halfway through.  Transfer to a clean cutting board and cut the sandwiches in half.  Enjoy!   Yield: 2 sandwiches
